      "type": "grammar_spotlight",
      "content": "In the second poem, we see **しらぬ (shiranu)**. \n1. Verb: **しる** (shiru - to know / 知).\n2. Mizenkei: **しら** (shira).\n3. Negative: **ぬ** (nu).\n\nWhy **ぬ** instead of **ず**? Because it is acting as a noun ('those who do NOT know'). As we learned in Unit 3, the **Rentaikei** (Attributive form) is required to turn a verb into a noun-phrase or modify a noun. For the negative auxiliary, the Rentaikei is **ぬ**.",
